-- Hove Leaves Stifel for Clarus; GMP Hires Stevenson, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-10-04T19:02:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-04/hove-leaves-stifel-for-clarus-gmp-hires-stevenson-vlaad-says.html
Richard Nadeau, former Desjardins
Securities Inc. vice chairman and managing director of  capital
markets , is now chief financial officer of Groupe Reseau
Selection, according to Vlaad & Co., a Toronto-based financial
services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  * Marwan Kubursi joined Cormark Securities Inc. to head
technology, clean tech and health-care investment banking.
Kubursi was formerly a managing director of investment banking
at Stifel Financial Corp.  * Former UBS AG bankers Kurtis Shumka and Jamie Wilkie are now
at Wells Fargo & Co.  * Scott Yester was hired as an investment banking analyst at
Haywood Securities Inc. He was previously at Lululemon Athletica
Inc. in its e-commerce division.  * Brett Stevenson moved from 32 Degrees Capital to GMP
Securities LLC as an  investment-banking  associate.  * Raymond James Financial Inc. hired Kurt Molnar as an energy
equity analyst from Stifel.  * Dave Hove, formerly with Stifel, joined Clarus Securities Inc.
as a mining research associate.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
